	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="R 6457-71 (55)"/>
			<p>It is learned from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName> that many of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> among the 450,000 in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> there are shortly to be placed in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term> in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1157" type="subject">country districts</term> where they will be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">forced to work</term> on highway, land and forest
				improvement projects. Public notices have been posted asking for young <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_poles">Poles</term> to
				volunteer for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1126" type="subject">special police</term> units to guard
				these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camps and working parties</term>. The use of
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">Jewish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">labor</term> on these projects will release the
				equivalent amount of <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">labor</term> for employment in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">Reich</term> as <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">agricultural</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">industrial</term> workers.</p>
		</body>
